Program A 

Ball will bounce off of the sides of the screen, and the user will be able to draw obstacles with their mouse.

Mandatory Requirements:
Ball must move, collide with obstacles, bounce off walls.
Mouse must draw obstacles that can interact with the ball if it’s larger than 3 pixels.
Ensure that if an obstacle is less than 3 pixels that it doesn’t affect the ball. 
Ball program must work with a wide number of window sizes. Eg. resolutions.
Add a reset ball button to fix any problems like the ball getting stuck.


Optional Requirements: 
Ball makes a sound when bouncing off an obstacle.
Customizable ball sizes/colors.
Add visual effects to the ball when it moves or bounces off obstacles.
Make the ball never hit the corners of the window.
